---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../components/Article.astro";
import { Code } from "astro:components";
import "../styles/global.css";
import "../styles/font.css";
import Heading from "../components/Heading.astro";
// import Article from "../components/Article.astro";

import FDC_wobble from "../components/DancingLetters/FDC_wobble.astro";
import FDC_flicker from "../components/DancingLetters/FDC_flicker.astro";
import FDC_disco from "../components/DancingLetters/FDC_disco2.astro";
import FDC_neon from "../components/DancingLetters/FDC_neon.astro";
import FDC_spinning from "../components/DancingLetters/FDC_spinning.astro";
import FDC_seventy from "../components/DancingLetters/FDC_seventy.astro";
---

<Layout title="Dancing Letters">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-literata font-bold text-center mt-10 mb-10">
        <span class="dance">D</span>ancing Letters
    </h1>
    <div class="flex justify-center items-start mb-20">
        <Article>
            <p>
                When creating a website for Forr√≥ da Capita, I played with some
                ideas for an animated logo. Here are some of the CSS animations
                I pieced together.
            </p>
            <p>
                The main thing to know about CSS animations is that your CSS
                styles (font size, color, position, width, height, etc.) can
                vary and change animated. A keyframe allows you to define the
                stages of your animation. For example, three different colors
                that your element passes through, or two positions it should
                traverse.
            </p>
            <p>
                Once you have the keyframes the transition needs a duration in
                which the stages are reeled off. Additionally, the animation may
                be given a delay, a direction, an iteration/repetition, and a
                timing function.
            </p>
            <p>
                Have a look at the options at <a
                    href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_animations.asp"
                    >w3schools</a
                >. For instance, check out <a
                    href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_2dtransforms.asp"
                    >2D</a
                > and <a
                    href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_3dtransforms.asp"
                    >3D</a
                > transforms, that allow you to rotate, scale, move (translate),
                and skew elements. Combine this with colors, and you already have
                ample possibilities.
            </p>
        </Article>
    </div>

    <!-- WOBBLE  -->
    <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 w-full justify-between items-start gap-10 mt-15"
    >
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
            <FDC_wobble />
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-2 justify-center items-center">
            <Article>
                For a haggish wobble, single letters are shifted up and down,
                starting with a little lag one after another. For that bubbling
                cauldron effect the letters are also bloated / shrinked (<Code
                    code={`scale`}
                    lang="css"
                    theme="one-light"
                    inline
                />) and rotated a little.
            </Article>

            <!-- WOBBLE CODE  -->
            <details class="w-full mt-2">
                <summary class="text-xl font-work mb-2 tracking-wide"
                    >CODE</summary
                >
                <div class="w-full h-60 overflow-scroll resize-y rounded-md">
                    <Code
                        class:list={["px-10 py-5"]}
                        lang="html"
                        theme="one-light"
                        wrap
                        code={`
<div class="wobble">
    <span>W</span>
    <span>O</span>
    <span>B</span>
    <span>B</span>
    <span>L</span>
    <span>E</span>
</div>

<style>
@font-face {
    font-family: "Oi";
    src: url("/fonts/HennyPenny-Regular.ttf") format("truetype");
    font-display: swap;
}

.wobble {
    font-family: "Oi";
    font-size: 3rem;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    display: inline-flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
}

.wobble span {
    display: inline-block;
    animation: wobble 1.6s infinite ease-in-out;
    transition: width 3s height 3s ease-in-out 3s;
    will-change: transform;
}

/* The keyframes for wobble */
@keyframes wobble {
    0%,
    100% { transform: translateY(0) rotate(0deg) scale(1); }
    20% { transform: translateY(-4px) rotate(-2deg) scale(1.01); }
    50% { transform: translateY(4px) rotate(2deg) scale(0.99); }
    80% { transform: translateY(-3px) rotate(-2deg) scale(1.03); }
}

/* Different delays for each letter */
.wobble span:nth-child(1) {
    animation-delay: 0s;
}
.wobble span:nth-child(2) {
    animation-delay: 0.1s;
}
.wobble span:nth-child(3) {
    animation-delay: 0.2s;
}
.wobble span:nth-child(4) {
    animation-delay: 0.3s;
}
.wobble span:nth-child(5) {
    animation-delay: 0.4s;
}
.wobble span:nth-child(6) {
    animation-delay: 0.5s;
}
</style>
            `}
                    />
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DISCO -->
    <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 w-full justify-between items-start gap-10 mt-15"
    >
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
            <FDC_disco />
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-2 justify-center items-center">
            <Article>
                <p>
                    Hover over the letters and each will shine in a disco light.
                    The glow is produced by stacking multiple text-shadow layers
                    with progressively larger blurs and slight color variations
                    around the text.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Text-shadow takes four values: <br />
                    <Code
                        code={`text-shadow: [horizontal-offset] [vertical-offset] [blur-radius] [color];`}
                        lang="css"
                        theme="one-light"
                        inline
                    />
                </p>
            </Article>

            <!-- DISCO CODE  -->
            <details class="w-full mt-2">
